# PixiJS v8 + bitECS — Aikami Compilation Constraints

## Game Zone (Imperative — No Svelte)
- Directory `apps/frontend/client/src/lib/game/` is Svelte-free. ZERO `$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`. Pure imperative TypeScript.
- 60fps loop runs via `requestAnimationFrame`. Any `$state` in game code triggers DOM re-render every frame.

## ECS Data Ownership
- bitECS owns data. PixiJS reads it each frame.
- Store PixiJS display objects in `Map<number, DisplayObject>` — NEVER in bitECS typed arrays.
- bitECS SoA arrays hold numbers only.

## Engine Bridge Boundary
- All Svelte ↔ game communication via EngineBridge typed message channel.
- Svelte side: `GameCommand →` (send). `GameEvent ←` (listen).
- Game side: handles commands, emits events at UI-relevant intervals only (seconds, not per-frame).
- Payloads: plain serializable objects ONLY. NO class instances, functions, PixiJS objects, bitECS handles.

## ViewModels — No Ticker Hooks
- ViewModels in `$views/` must NOT hook into `app.ticker` or any per-frame callback directly.
- Rendering ticker tasks belong in `packages/frontend/engine/` — the central engine package abstracts the ticker.
- ViewModels expose reactive property bindings for the engine bridge to write into at UI-relevant intervals.
- If a ViewModel needs per-frame data, the engine bridge pushes batched state diffs, not raw frame data.

## Forbidden Patterns
- NO `$state` in `apps/frontend/client/src/lib/game/`
- NO PixiJS imports in Svelte views or ViewModels
- NO `Sprite`, `Container`, `Texture` crossing the EngineBridge
- NO `app.ticker.add()` in ViewModels or views
- NO per-frame event emission across bridge (position updates, animation frames)
